[SN]TITLE[SN]
1,000 attend funeral of Celsa steelworker Peter O'Brien

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
More than 1,000 people attended the funeral of one of two men killed in a steelworks explosion in Cardiff.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Peter O'Brien, 51, of Llanishen, Cardiff, and Mark Sim, 41, of Caldicot, Monmouthshire, died in the blast at Celsa Steel UK last month.
Canon Matthew Jones said at least 1,000 people attended Mr O'Brien's funeral at Christ the King Church, Llanishen, on Thursday.
Mr Sim's funeral will take place at Forest of Dean Crematorium on Tuesday.
Mr O'Brien has been described by his family as a "treasured and respected" man.
